{
    "comment_thread": {}, 
    "video_length": "PT4M46S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Everyone has something\nthat motivates them.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For some people \nit&#39;s money.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For some,\nit may be recognition,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and others,\nmaybe chocolate.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you&#39;re one \nof my research animals,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s the beloved Froot Loop.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They absolutely love \nthese as treats.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;re easy for them \nto put in their mouth,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and most importantly,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they&#39;re packed with sugar.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In our lab, we study\nthe brain chemical dopamine.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Dopamine is involved in movement,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "most notably implicated\nin Parkinson&#39;s disease,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "motivation and reward.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We study dopamine", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in relation to learning\nand memory tasks.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our rats learn\nto run in a maze,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and if they complete\nthe task correctly,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they receive \na food reward at the end.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We study and record\nwhen dopamine is released", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as the rats are completing\nthis task.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Look, he is even smiling!\n(Laughter)", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Dopamine helps activate\nthe learning centers in the brain.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if dopamine is released", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as you&#39;re learning something,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it will help you \nremember that information", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at a later date.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For example,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I had a chemistry professor \non the very first day of class,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "do an intense reaction\nwith lots of flames and smoke.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He then explained", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how and why this chemical \nreaction took place.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This reaction was done", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "just using regular \ntap water and sodium.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After he explained \nhow this reaction worked,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll never forget exactly", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how those electrons\nare moved in that reaction.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is likely that as this reaction\nwas taking place,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dopamine was being released\nin my brain.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Of course, since I don&#39;t have\nany of our lab&#39;s electrodes", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "placed in my brain,\nwe won&#39;t know for sure.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "On the left\nis a picture of the electrodes", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we build in our lab.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The electrode end consists \nof a single strand of carbon fiber.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s about one-tenth the diameter\nof the strand of human hair.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We then implant these electrodes", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in freely moving animals,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and record\nwhen dopamine is released,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as they complete maze tasks.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As you can see,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the rat brain is very small.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s about the size of a nickel.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the area of the brain\nthat we&#39;re trying to reach,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is about the size of a pea.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We implant these electrodes\nin an area of the brain,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s known to have\na high number of dopamine neurons.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One of my main hobbies \nis photography.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, \nfor the background of my talk,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I thought I would take you\nall on a tour of my lab,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by way of my photography.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These are just\na few of the things", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we use in our lab", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to help us record dopamine.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So what can we do \nto increase dopamine in our brain?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Exercise, is a great way\nto increase dopamine.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Exercise will increase \ndopamine release in your brain,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as well as other neurochemicals,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "such as endorphins", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which are the brain&#39;s \nnatural painkillers.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Eating properly,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is another great way \nto increase dopamine.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Specifically, \neating foods rich in tyrosine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is a precursor to dopamine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "will help, increase the available \ndopamine in the brain.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Foods rich in tyrosine", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "include things such as: Avocados,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "almonds and bananas.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Another great way \nto release dopamine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is doing something \nrewarding to you.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This can be something", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as easy as checking something \noff your to-do list,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or perhaps volunteering\nat a community center.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And of course,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one of my personal favorite ways,\nto increase dopamine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is sex.\n(Laughter)", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sex releases many beneficial\nchemicals in the brain", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in addition to dopamine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "such as oxytocin,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is implicated \nin human bonding.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Serotonin,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which relates to happiness\nand a feeling of well-being.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And norepinephrine,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which increases alertness.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how can we use\nthis information?", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Professors can develop \nnew and exciting ways,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to deliver information to students.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It doesn&#39;t have \nto be as exciting", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as involving flames and explosions", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like my chemistry professor.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It can be as simple as", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "having students \ndo a hands-on experience,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or perhaps using\nthe students as props", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to explain a difficult concept.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Professors, get away\nfrom the traditional monologue lectures.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;ll be more rewarding\nfor you,", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and will stimulate the students\nto promote long-term learning.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s get\nthose dopamine neurons firing.", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thank you.\n(Applause)", 
            "dur": 0, 
            "start": 0
        }
